== 环境影响 ==
提高的采油井通常将大量的采出水泵送到地表面。 这种水含有[[盐|盐]]，也可能含有有毒重金属和[[放射性|放射性]]物质<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Igunnu |first1=Ebenezer T. |last2=Chen |first2=George Z. |date=2012-07-04 |title=Produced water treatment technologies |url=http://ijlct.oxfordjournals.org/content/9/3/157 |journal=Int. J. Low-Carbon Tech. |publisher=Oxford University Press |volume=2014 |issue=9 |page=157 |doi=10.1093/ijlct/cts049 |access-date=2018-06-19 |archive-date=2016-12-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161228084252/http://ijlct.oxfordjournals.org/content/9/3/157 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。 如果没有适当的控制，这可能会对饮用水源和环境造成很大的损害。 处置井(Disposal wells)被用于通过将采出水注入地下而防止土壤和水的表面污染<ref name="EPA UIC">{{cite web |url=http://www.epa.gov/uic/class-ii-oil-and-gas-related-injection-wells |title=Class II Oil and Gas Related Injection Wells |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2015-10-08 |website=Underground Injection Control |publisher=US Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) |location=Washington, D.C. |access-date=2018-06-19 |archive-date=2021-03-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210324233003/https://www.epa.gov/uic/class-ii-oil-and-gas-related-injection-wells |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Gleason|first1=Robert A.|last2=Tangen|first2=Brian A.|title=Brine Contamination to Aquatic Resources from Oil and Gas Development in the Williston Basin, United States|date=2014|publisher=United States Geological Survey|location=Reston, VA|url=https://purl.fdlp.gov/GPO/gpo49778|accessdate=15 June 2014}}</ref>。

在美国，注入井活动由[[美国国家环境保护局|美国国家环境保护局]]（EPA）和州政府根据《{{le|安全饮用水法|Safe Drinking Water Act}}》进行管理<ref name="EPA Basicinfo">{{cite web |url=http://www.epa.gov/uic/general-information-about-injection-wells |title=General Information About Injection Wells |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2015-10-08 |publisher=EPA |access-date=2018-06-19 |archive-date=2021-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210318173448/https://www.epa.gov/uic/general-information-about-injection-wells |dead-url=no }}</ref>。美国国家环境保护局已经颁布了地下注射控制（UIC）规定，以保护饮用水源<ref name="EPA Regs">{{cite web |url=http://www.epa.gov/uic/underground-injection-control-regulations |title=Underground Injection Control Regulations |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2015-10-05 |publisher=EPA |access-date=2018-06-19 |archive-date=2021-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210323014700/https://www.epa.gov/uic/underground-injection-control-regulations |dead-url=no }}</ref>。美国国家环境保护局将提高采收率的油井作为“II类”井进行管理。 这些法规要求井操作人员将第二类处理井中用于地下深处回收的盐水重新回注。

